# CFA-DeepLabV3+: Cross-level Fusion and Attention Network for Lightweight Road Segmentation

This repository contains the official implementation of our paper **"CFA-DeepLabV3+: Cross-level Fusion and Attention Network for Lightweight Road Segmentation"**. We provide the code, dataset preparation instructions, and pretrained models for road segmentation.

## 📌 Overview

Road segmentation is a critical task in autonomous driving and intelligent navigation systems. In this work, we propose **CFA-DeepLabV3+**, a lightweight network that integrates cross-level feature fusion and attention mechanisms to achieve accurate and efficient road segmentation under diverse scenarios.

## 📊 Dataset

We build our dataset based on the **Indian Driving Dataset (IDD)** [19], refining it to 19 road-related categories. To enhance diversity, we extend it with additional scenes including forest roads, woodland trails, and indoor corridors. The final dataset contains **4,389 high-resolution (1024×1024) images** with pixel-level annotations. The data is organized in a single folder named **`_cityRoad`**, containing image-mask pairs with consistent naming.
